  abstract={Since colonial times, modern scholarship of Korean antiquity always had a “heterodox” tradition that depicted a much more expansive scope of ancient Korean states and cultures than their “orthodox” counterparts. I present a detailed and up-to-date history of historiography of Old Chosŏn and Lelang Commandery that tracks the diachronic development of both traditions and how their boundaries shifted over time and interacted with each other. Close attention is paid to the influence of external factors as much as internal.}
